1
00:00:01,280 --> 00:00:02,380
singers:
♪ mori, mori, mori, mori

2
00:00:02,410 --> 00:00:04,550
♪ morioh Cho radio

3
00:00:04,580 --> 00:00:06,650
- ♪ morioh Cho radio
- Kai: Rise and shine.

4
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:08,450
Welcome to morioh radio.

5
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:11,050
as usual,
this is your host, Kai harada,

6
00:00:11,090 --> 00:00:13,590
keeping you company
on this fine morning,

7
00:00:13,620 --> 00:00:16,790
and i’ve got just the song
to start you off right.

8
00:00:16,820 --> 00:00:18,760
- ( Rock ballad playing )
- ( Snipping )

9
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:28,700
( Snipping continues )

10
00:00:28,740 --> 00:00:34,640
- ♪ Babe, I will
take you anywhere... ♪

11
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:37,180
Kira: Now let’s dig in,
shall we?

12
00:00:37,210 --> 00:00:40,820
Oh, but before we begin, I have
a little something for you.

13
00:00:40,850 --> 00:00:47,220
♪ And i’m here
to make you smile ♪

14
00:00:47,260 --> 00:00:53,260
♪ and i’m here hanging down

15
00:00:53,290 --> 00:00:59,270
♪ babe, all your lies,
I will survive ♪

16
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,640
- ( Music crackling )
- ♪ babe...

17
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:04,410
♪

18
00:01:09,510 --> 00:01:11,680
( Singing in Japanese )

19
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:42,180
Woman: Excuse me. Mr. Kira?

20
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:44,480
♪

21
00:01:46,210 --> 00:01:47,550
Kira: Hmm?

22
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:49,780
Woman: Mr. Kira, I know
this is super last-minute,

23
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:52,390
but would you be interested
in getting lunch with us?

24
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:55,820
Kira: Apologies,
but I must decline.

25
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:58,230
i need to finish
delivering these documents

26
00:01:58,260 --> 00:01:59,990
before the day
gets away from me.

27
00:02:00,030 --> 00:02:01,700
Enjoy your lunch.

28
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,700
Man: Don’t waste
your time on him.

29
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:06,200
Woman: Hmm?

30
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:08,670
Man: He’d suck the life
out of the party.

31
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,810
the guys and I
invite him out on occasion,

32
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:13,710
but we can never tell
if he’s having fun or hates us.

33
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:17,350
Yoshikage Kira, age 33, single.

34
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:19,880
He’s a model employee,
that’s for damn sure,

35
00:02:19,910 --> 00:02:21,780
but the guy’s
dull as dishwater.

36
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:24,650
it’s not that he’s
necessarily a tool or anything.

37
00:02:24,690 --> 00:02:27,390
He’s just kind of blah,
you know?

38
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:29,620
♪

39
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,000
Kira: Oh, is that right?

40
00:02:35,030 --> 00:02:37,370
Someone’s a little
bent out of shape.

41
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,530
Some new girls at work
invited me to lunch.

42
00:02:39,570 --> 00:02:41,570
really,
it’s as innocent as that.

43
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:44,970
but I promised you
lunch was our time together.

44
00:02:45,010 --> 00:02:48,840
I’d never go back on my word
just to fraternize with them.

45
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:51,580
You heard me turn them down,
didn’t you?

46
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:53,650
in the time
we’ve known each other,

47
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:57,490
i’ve never left you
by your lonesome, right?

48
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,620
Good. It’s settled.

49
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:00,920
Now stop this silly fretting,

50
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,960
and let’s pick out
some sandwiches.

51
00:03:02,990 --> 00:03:04,990
Now, which one do you want?

52
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:07,700
mmm, this one
has a delicate texture.

53
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:09,700
This bakery’s
one of my favorites.

54
00:03:09,730 --> 00:03:12,730
It makes sandwiches with bread
made fresh at 11 A.M.

55
00:03:12,770 --> 00:03:14,440
They’re all the rage
around here.

56
00:03:14,470 --> 00:03:17,410
You’d be lucky to find one
on the shelf after 1 P.M.

57
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,840
Even through the wrapper,

58
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:20,810
you can feel
they’re fresh from the oven.

59
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,310
The katsu they use

60
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:24,950
is always freshly fried
and perfectly crispy.

61
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:28,280
What have we here?

62
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,820
It seems in all the excitement,

63
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:32,690
you managed to tear the wrapper
and make a mess.

64
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,820
Hmm. Such a naughty girl.

65
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:36,660
♪

66
00:03:37,790 --> 00:03:39,690
( Shudders )

67
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,530
Ah...

68
00:03:45,570 --> 00:03:47,500
( Sighing, slurping )

69
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:53,610
it’s a waste,
but this sandwich is ruined now.

70
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:56,380
i suppose we’ll
just buy the one underneath.

71
00:03:56,410 --> 00:03:58,780
Clerk: Thank you
for dropping by.

72
00:03:58,810 --> 00:04:00,650
♪

73
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,690
( Birds chirping )

74
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:12,560
( Kira chewing )

75
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:14,900
Simply beautiful, isn’t it?

76
00:04:14,930 --> 00:04:16,760
Quaint, little morioh.

77
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:20,770
Between us, it might be the most
marvelous town on earth.

78
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,510
It’s like we’re
on a romantic picnic.

79
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:26,010
( Gasps )

80
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:28,540
( Sniffing )

81
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:31,550
( Grumbling )

82
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:36,380
( Sniffs )

83
00:04:36,420 --> 00:04:39,320
A bit aromatic for my taste.

84
00:04:39,350 --> 00:04:42,390
i think it’s time
for the two of us to part ways.

85
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:43,990
The end is close at hand.

86
00:04:44,030 --> 00:04:46,490
"Close at hand." ( Chuckles )

87
00:04:46,530 --> 00:04:49,660
If luck is on my side,
perhaps i’ll cross paths

88
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:52,870
with a beautiful new girl
visiting from out of town.

89
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,070
- ( Brush rustles )
- huh?

90
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:56,940
♪

91
00:04:56,970 --> 00:04:59,540
( Dog panting )

92
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:01,610
Kira: Oh, joy. It’s a mutt.

93
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:05,480
♪

94
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:06,910
( Dog whimpers )

95
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:18,960
( Chewing )

96
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,430
- Josuke: Huh?
- Okuyasu: Shigechi!

97
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:24,430
Shigechi: Eh?

98
00:05:24,470 --> 00:05:26,370
Hey!

99
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,870
Josuke and okuyasu,
good to see you.

100
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,670
Okuyasu: What’s up? You know,

101
00:05:30,710 --> 00:05:32,810
you got here
just in the Nick of time.

102
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,780
josuke: I’ll get
right to the point, okay?

103
00:05:34,810 --> 00:05:36,510
We need to borrow
some lunch money.

104
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:38,610
We’re a little strapped for cash
at the moment.

105
00:05:38,650 --> 00:05:40,880
shigechi: Huh?
How’s that even possible?

106
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,550
What happened to the money
we got from the lottery ticket?

107
00:05:43,590 --> 00:05:44,690
Is it gone already?

108
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,050
Okuyasu: Don’t be silly!

109
00:05:46,090 --> 00:05:48,590
We put all that in the bank,
and you gotta be crazy

110
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:50,830
if you think we’d go
all the way to the bank

111
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:53,130
just to get some lunch money.
It’s not worth the walk.

112
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:55,200
A thousand yen should be
enough for both of us.

113
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:56,800
Josuke: I agree.

114
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,700
okuyasu: Come on.
As soon as school’s over,

115
00:05:58,730 --> 00:06:00,500
we’ll head to the bank
and pay you back.

116
00:06:00,540 --> 00:06:02,370
Josuke: Hey, I know that logo.

117
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,540
you got a sandwich
from St. gentlemen, didn’t you?

118
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:05,970
- okuyasu: Whoa!
- Josuke: Well, whaddaya know.

119
00:06:06,010 --> 00:06:07,840
- I thought they were sold out.
- Shigechi: They are,

120
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,510
and you’re not getting a single
bite of mine! You got that?

121
00:06:10,550 --> 00:06:12,450
Eh, if you leave
my sandwich alone,

122
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,980
i’ll lend you guys the money.

123
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:15,150
Josuke: Sweet!

124
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:16,720
Okuyasu: I can taste
our lunch already.

125
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:19,390
Josuke: Thank you.

126
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:20,720
Shigechi: And just so you know,

127
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,890
i’m writing an I.O.U.
For this little loan.

128
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,890
You’re not gonna
weasel out of this one.

129
00:06:24,930 --> 00:06:27,630
okuyasu: Me? You’re
the biggest weasel there is!

130
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:28,730
Shigechi: Okay. "June 24th..."

131
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,060
Josuke: Thanks a lot, shigechi.

132
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:33,200
Shigechi: "Lent 1,000 yen
to needy friends."

133
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:35,070
Hang on. "Lent."

134
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:37,570
How do you write the character
for "lent" again?

135
00:06:37,610 --> 00:06:38,970
Oh, well. This’ll work for now.

136
00:06:40,610 --> 00:06:42,980
I guess hiragana’s
better than nothing.

137
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:44,210
Crud monkeys. I don’t know

138
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,750
how to write "josuke"
or "okuyasu" either.

139
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:48,180
Eh? What the?!

140
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:51,650
My sandwich was right there!
Where did it go?

141
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:53,190
( Gasping )

142
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:55,790
♪

143
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,090
( Sighs )

144
00:06:57,130 --> 00:07:00,560
what a relief.
My sandwich is safe and sound.

145
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,130
I don’t remember it
being this far away,

146
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:05,670
but at least I found it.

147
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:06,670
Kira: Huh?

148
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:08,000
Hmm?

149
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,670
( Gasps )

150
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:12,470
♪

151
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,880
( Shigechi panting )

152
00:07:13,910 --> 00:07:15,140
Kira: Th-that’s...

153
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:18,650
Shigechi: Hey, josuke,
okuyasu, wait up!

154
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,120
We’re not done yet!

155
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:22,950
I need your thumbprints on
my I.O.U. To make it official!

156
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:23,950
Kira: Huh?

157
00:07:23,990 --> 00:07:25,690
( Dog grunting )

158
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:29,990
Kira: You have
got to be kidding me.

159
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:33,160
That lump of a brat
grabbed my bag by mistake.

160
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:35,860
josuke: Come on.
Could you be any more annoying?

161
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:37,270
How would we give you
our thumbprints?

162
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,830
Okuyasu: It’s simple.

163
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:41,070
You cut your thumb with a knife
and use the blood.

164
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,240
Shigechi: What are
you talking about?!

165
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,840
We don’t have to go that far.

166
00:07:43,870 --> 00:07:46,170
Just sign the I.O.U.,
and we’ll call it good.

167
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:48,940
Okuyasu: Yeah, yeah, but let’s
haul ass to St. gentlemen

168
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:50,050
before they sell out.

169
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,580
Kira: Damn it.

170
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:53,780
I can’t let him see
what’s in that bag.

171
00:07:53,820 --> 00:07:57,650
She’s still wearing the ring I
put on her finger this morning.

172
00:07:57,690 --> 00:07:59,590
It has my fingerprints on it,

173
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:01,660
so when the police
open an investigation,

174
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:04,990
it’ll be just a matter of time
before they trace it back to me.

175
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:11,830
yoshikage Kira
has been at this for 15 years,

176
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:14,900
and in all that time,
he’s never left a single clue.

177
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:17,510
This pathetic whelp
isn’t changing that.

178
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:19,670
Okuyasu: Hey, josuke,
let’s head in.

179
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:21,110
Josuke: Right.

180
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:23,710
Shigechi: I’ll stay outside
and wait for you guys.

181
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:28,720
Kira: My best bet
is to take it by force.

182
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:31,720
On second thought, i’d better
snatch it without his knowing.

183
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:34,260
♪

184
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:38,130
Okuyasu: Shigechi!

185
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:40,630
You’re a lucky son of a gun.
You know that?

186
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:42,330
Josuke: The lunchtime rush
beat us here,

187
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,630
and they’re already out
of St. gentlemen sandwiches.

188
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:45,730
Just our luck.

189
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:47,000
Shigechi: They’re sold out, huh?

190
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,770
( Mocking )
Well, isn’t that a shame?

191
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:51,070
I feel bad for you guys.
i really do.

192
00:08:51,110 --> 00:08:53,640
I guess I could sell you mine,
but, so you know,

193
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,980
it’ll cost you 10,000 yen. ’kay?

194
00:08:56,010 --> 00:08:58,150
- ( Laughs )
- ( Kira growling )

195
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:01,280
Okuyasu: Boy, not a decent bone
in your body, is there?

196
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:04,190
All right, josuke, looks like
we’re heading to hokaben.

197
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:05,920
Josuke: You sure
that’ll be enough?

198
00:09:05,950 --> 00:09:09,060
I doubt a 500-yen meal
and a drink will fill us up.

199
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,560
We’re better off skipping it.

200
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:11,890
It’s not my first choice,

201
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:13,900
but the cafeteria
will do just fine.

202
00:09:13,930 --> 00:09:16,330
Besides, that’s where koichi
said he’s getting lunch today.

203
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,930
Okuyasu: Aw, man,

204
00:09:17,970 --> 00:09:20,070
that means he’ll be there
with yukako yamagishi.

205
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,970
I hate having to be
the third wheel

206
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,710
to those honeymooners’s
lovefest.

207
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:26,870
And the food they serve
is terrible.

208
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:29,640
Their nasty meat is so thin,
it’s practically invisible.

209
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:32,780
And who knows what kinda weird
shit they put in the miso soup?

210
00:09:32,810 --> 00:09:34,750
Shigechi: Hey! Why don’t we
use the equipment room

211
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,920
at my middle school’s gym?

212
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,020
It has tons of drinks
to choose from.

213
00:09:38,050 --> 00:09:39,820
Our p.E. Teacher
always sneaks away

214
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:42,290
to have his coffee and tea
in there when no one’s looking.

215
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:44,790
All the teachers are in
the faculty room during lunch,

216
00:09:44,830 --> 00:09:46,730
so they won’t
be able to bust us.

217
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,260
Sometimes i’ll sneak in
through the window

218
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,170
and take a cup
to quench my thirst.

219
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,700
Why don’t you go buy lunch,

220
00:09:51,730 --> 00:09:53,200
and we’ll hang out there
and eat together.

221
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:55,070
Josuke: Let’s back it up there,
shigechi.

222
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:57,240
are you seriously
stealing drinks from school?

223
00:09:57,270 --> 00:09:58,940
Okuyasu: You stingy bastard!

224
00:09:58,970 --> 00:10:01,040
can’t you even
buy drinks for yourself?

225
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,340
you’d never see me
doing something that greedy.

226
00:10:03,380 --> 00:10:04,810
See you later.

227
00:10:04,850 --> 00:10:07,080
shigechi: Jeez,
what crawled up their butts?

228
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,420
I was just trying to be nice.

229
00:10:08,450 --> 00:10:10,420
Okay, well...

230
00:10:10,450 --> 00:10:13,420
You better pay me back
my thousand yen tomorrow!

231
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:15,860
♪

232
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:16,990
Hmph.

233
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:19,690
- ( Kira gasps )
- ( Shigechi gasps )

234
00:10:25,170 --> 00:10:27,240
Sorry for bumping
into you, sir.

235
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:30,240
It’s all my fault. I wasn’t
looking where I was going.

236
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:32,210
Sorry again.

237
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,710
Kira: Shit, so close.

238
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:37,810
He’s left his idiotic friends,
but he’s heading back to school.

239
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:41,950
He’s eating lunch there,
so what’s my next move?

240
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:45,920
i believe
they call him shigechi.

241
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:47,920
Minutes from now,
he’ll open that bag,

242
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:50,130
and things will get
very complicated.

243
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:53,160
Damn it. This is unfathomable.

244
00:10:53,190 --> 00:10:55,130
( Shigechi chuckling )

245
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:11,950
all righty, now that
i’m in my special hidey spot,

246
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,480
i can finally
eat my lunch in peace.

247
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,920
♪

248
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:22,260
( Kira gasps )

249
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:23,490
Shigechi: Oh, yeah.

250
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,060
How did I almost forget?

251
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:27,200
before I start
chowing down on my food,

252
00:11:27,230 --> 00:11:28,500
I need to make coffee.

253
00:11:28,530 --> 00:11:30,200
It’s not a secret trip
to the gym

254
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:32,000
without a freshly brewed cup.

255
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:33,970
( Chuckling )

256
00:11:38,170 --> 00:11:40,810
Kira: Fortune has smiled
on you, shigechi.

257
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,410
Had you peaked inside,

258
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:45,310
my only recourse would have
been to obliterate you.

259
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:47,280
♪

260
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:53,790
okuyasu: Josuke,
I think this is the place.

261
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:55,290
- ( Kira gasps )
- ( Okuyasu grunts )

262
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,030
It’s smaller than I thought.

263
00:11:57,060 --> 00:11:58,030
Kira: What the?

264
00:11:58,060 --> 00:11:59,390
Why are they here?

265
00:11:59,430 --> 00:12:01,260
I thought these two
were blowing him off.

266
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:06,200
Okuyasu: Shigechi,
you here or what?

267
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:07,470
Shigechi!

268
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,970
Shigechi: Huh? Hey,
what are you doing here?

269
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,210
i thought you were
gonna get lunch somewhere else.

270
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,410
Josuke: That was the plan,
but we couldn’t just pass up

271
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,380
free coffee from café gym.

272
00:12:16,410 --> 00:12:18,950
Okuyasu: We got 500-yen
makunouchi bentos on the way.

273
00:12:18,980 --> 00:12:20,010
( Laughs )

274
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:22,020
Shigechi: Wow, I can’t believe

275
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:23,450
you two actually
showed up to eat

276
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,850
after calling me
a stingy bastard.

277
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,860
you’re a couple
of hypocritical pricks.

278
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:29,560
Josuke: Come on, man.
Cut us some slack.

279
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:31,930
haven’t you heard
of people changing their minds?

280
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,060
it is a thing
that happens, you know?

281
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,960
( Kira groans )

282
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,600
Now what do I do?

283
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:40,240
offing one of them
would be a walk in the park,

284
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:42,570
but I can’t tackle
all three at once.

285
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:45,070
Shit. I was so close, too.

286
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:47,110
She’s only centimeters away.

287
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:49,580
- ( Clatter )
- Kira: Huh?

288
00:12:49,610 --> 00:12:52,410
josuke: Shigechi,
you mind grabbing me a drink

289
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:54,020
on your way back?

290
00:12:54,050 --> 00:12:56,620
and could you make it
a green tea instead of coffee?

291
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,920
Okuyasu: I’ll take
a black tea with milk.

292
00:12:58,950 --> 00:13:01,120
shigechi: Really?
Makunouchi with milk tea?

293
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,860
That sounds disgusting.

294
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:05,330
Kira: Shit! He’s going
to try to eat his meal

295
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,000
right on top of this thing.

296
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:08,530
If I don’t do something fast,

297
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:11,230
he’s going to open the bag
right in front of them. Huh?

298
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:22,510
okuyasu: Aw,
not soy sauce again.

299
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:25,550
They’re always givin’ me
soy sauce with katsu.

300
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:28,020
Josuke: Huh? That’s how
you’re supposed to eat it.

301
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:29,980
Okuyasu: No way!
Don’t be stupid.

302
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:32,090
Everyone knows
it’s tonkatsu sauce.

303
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:35,290
Putting soy sauce on tonkatsu
violates all that’s sacred.

304
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,320
Josuke: Like it matters.

305
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:38,860
♪

306
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,300
Kira: Yes.

307
00:13:50,470 --> 00:13:51,570
( Gasps )

308
00:13:54,510 --> 00:13:56,280
- Josuke: Hmm?
- Okuyasu: Eh?

309
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:57,480
Kira: Damn it.

310
00:13:57,510 --> 00:13:59,480
Josuke: What the hell?

311
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:01,380
♪

312
00:14:03,950 --> 00:14:05,390
- Okuyasu: Eh?

313
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:06,590
Kira: Damn it.

314
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:08,590
Josuke: What the hell?

315
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:10,590
♪

316
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:19,370
Shigechi: Just a minute!

317
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,340
What exactly do you
think you’re doing?

318
00:14:21,370 --> 00:14:24,140
Talk! ’cause from where
i’m standing, it looks like

319
00:14:24,170 --> 00:14:26,440
you’re trying to steal
my sandwich out from under me.

320
00:14:26,470 --> 00:14:28,580
josuke: As if!
Stop being such an idiot.

321
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:31,210
I came over here, ’cause I
thought I heard something weird.

322
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:33,550
I was gonna check it out
and then get back to eating.

323
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:35,620
Shigechi: My food’s
off limits, hear me?!

324
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:38,190
I can already hear
your sappy sob story.

325
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:40,420
"Teriyaki chicken sandwiches
are my favorite,

326
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:43,330
so won’t you please give me
a teeny-weeny bite, shigechi?"

327
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,630
Tell me i’m wrong!

328
00:14:44,660 --> 00:14:46,260
- You can’t, can you?
- ( Josuke groans )

329
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:48,330
You sure are a greedy
little stinker, aren’t you?

330
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,300
Why don’t you focus
on bringing out my tea?

331
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:52,070
Okuyasu: Oh, and don’t
forget my milk tea!

332
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,370
Shigechi: I’m making ’em
fast as I can.

333
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,400
( Grumbles )

334
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:00,240
Kira: Now.

335
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:02,210
♪

336
00:15:06,450 --> 00:15:07,920
Josuke: Eh?

337
00:15:07,950 --> 00:15:09,650
Kira: I did it.

338
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,590
shigechi: ’kay,
get ’em while they’re hot,

339
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:14,260
one green tea and
one black tea with milk.

340
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:15,660
- ( Okuyasu sighs )
- Josuke: Thanks.

341
00:15:15,690 --> 00:15:17,460
( Shigechi gasps )

342
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:18,460
Josuke: Eh?

343
00:15:18,490 --> 00:15:20,030
Okuyasu: What’s with you?

344
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:21,460
shigechi:
My sandwich disappeared!

345
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,670
What did you lunch thieves
do with it?!

346
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:25,530
okuyasu:
Lunch thieves? Who, us?

347
00:15:25,570 --> 00:15:27,040
Josuke: It’s definitely gone,

348
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:29,140
but we didn’t have
anything to do with it.

349
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:31,270
- Tell him, okuyasu.
- Okuyasu: What he said.

350
00:15:31,310 --> 00:15:33,180
Shigechi: I’ve had
enough of your games!

351
00:15:33,210 --> 00:15:34,510
There’s no one else here but us!

352
00:15:34,540 --> 00:15:36,380
you gotta know
what happened to my sandwich!

353
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:38,980
Josuke: We don’t! Seriously,
we’re telling you the truth.

354
00:15:39,010 --> 00:15:41,380
Okuyasu: Yeah, cross our hearts.
We’re not messin’ around.

355
00:15:41,420 --> 00:15:43,690
We’re just as confused
about all this as you are.

356
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,690
Shigechi: You lying punks.

357
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:48,090
Fine. Now you’ve gone
and made me angry.

358
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,690
Josuke: It’s the truth.

359
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:52,190
Okuyasu: I’ve had enough of you
pointing the finger at us.

360
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:54,160
Why would we take your sandwich
when we’ve got--

361
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,330
shigechi: If you’re gonna lie,
then we’ll do things my way!

362
00:15:57,370 --> 00:16:00,700
All I have to do is make harvest
turn this room inside out.

363
00:16:00,740 --> 00:16:02,670
Okuyasu: Damn,
you are so annoying.

364
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:05,210
Fine. Search the room.
i want you to.

365
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,380
Search until you pass out.
Go for it.

366
00:16:07,410 --> 00:16:08,510
Josuke: For the last time,

367
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:10,310
why would we steal
a stupid sandwich?

368
00:16:10,350 --> 00:16:13,050
♪

369
00:16:16,990 --> 00:16:18,250
Kira: This is torture.

370
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:19,650
What’s going on out there?

371
00:16:19,690 --> 00:16:22,690
I can’t see a thing
trapped under here.

372
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:25,290
I don’t know what
that pissant is up to,

373
00:16:25,330 --> 00:16:27,300
but it can’t be anything good.

374
00:16:27,330 --> 00:16:29,300
- Man: Hey, open up!
- ( Lock clicking )

375
00:16:29,330 --> 00:16:30,730
I know somebody’s in here!

376
00:16:30,770 --> 00:16:32,270
Shigechi: Shit balls!
we’re busted!

377
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:34,040
- It’s the p.E. Teacher!
- josuke: Crap!

378
00:16:34,070 --> 00:16:36,140
Then it’s time to bail!
let’s go!

379
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:38,710
Shigechi: I can’t leave! I still
haven’t found my sandwich!

380
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:40,380
Josuke: Now’s not the time!

381
00:16:40,410 --> 00:16:41,710
Out you go!

382
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:43,280
Teacher: Get back here!

383
00:16:43,310 --> 00:16:45,010
( Boys panting )

384
00:16:45,050 --> 00:16:46,180
Okuyasu: Let’s beat it!

385
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:48,520
( Teacher scoffs )
No-good hooligans.

386
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:52,020
I thought my tea and coffee
wasn’t lasting very long.

387
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:56,360
I thought I was going crazy,
but I was just being used.

388
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:59,090
I have to start
locking this place up

389
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:01,500
tighter than fort Knox.

390
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:04,430
( Footsteps )

391
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:09,440
( Door closes )

392
00:17:09,470 --> 00:17:12,370
♪

393
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:14,340
Kira: This day
has been hellacious,

394
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:17,040
but despite every setback,
I beat the odds

395
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:19,310
and have been reunited
with my girl.

396
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:22,550
i can’t explain it,
but i’ve always had the feeling

397
00:17:22,580 --> 00:17:25,050
that somewhere out there
is a guardian angel

398
00:17:25,090 --> 00:17:27,520
looking over
yoshikage kira’s shoulder,

399
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:31,130
that, in the end, things
will work out for the best

400
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:34,160
and, if I live every day
with rigor and boldness,

401
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:37,070
i’ll ultimately be delivered
from a wretched life.

402
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:39,070
( Chuckles )

403
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:42,170
We had a pretty close call
today, my dear,

404
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,410
but I knew we’d find
our way back to each other.

405
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:47,610
♪

406
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:50,550
- Shigechi: I found it.
- Kira: Hmm?

407
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:53,180
Shigechi: Now why is someone
i’ve never laid eyes on

408
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:55,150
skulking off with my sandwich?

409
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:57,050
and while we’re
on the subject, buster,

410
00:17:57,090 --> 00:17:59,450
why is some strange man
hanging around my school

411
00:17:59,490 --> 00:18:01,490
like it’s another day
at the office?

412
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:04,590
Kira: Pardon? You wouldn’t
happen to be talking to me,

413
00:18:04,630 --> 00:18:06,430
would you, little boy?

414
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:08,660
Because I haven’t
the faintest idea

415
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:10,130
what you’re going on about.

416
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:11,400
If you must know,

417
00:18:11,430 --> 00:18:13,630
I just purchased this item
at St. gentlemen.

418
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:15,370
Shigechi: You can save
the bullshit.

419
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,770
That bag’s my property.

420
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,770
I could go on and on
about how I know it’s mine,

421
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:22,410
but someone like you
would never understand.

422
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:24,810
Time to take back
what’s ours, harvest!

423
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:30,450
( Kira gasps ) Blast it!
What the hell is happening?

424
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:32,320
The bag’s being ripped away!

425
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:35,690
( Gasps )

426
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:38,590
( Shigechi gasps )

427
00:18:38,630 --> 00:18:41,430
Wait. What?! No way!

428
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:43,360
I don’t understand
what’s going on!

429
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,600
That’s not my sandwich!

430
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:46,330
Oh, god.

431
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:48,770
Did that hand come
from a real person?

432
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,410
Kira: So it’s come to this, eh?

433
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:53,880
My secret is out.

434
00:18:53,910 --> 00:18:56,540
Interestingly enough, you and I,

435
00:18:56,580 --> 00:19:00,320
it would appear that we both
share a unique power, but how?

436
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:03,120
Shigechi: What’d you just say?
Can you see my harvest?

437
00:19:03,150 --> 00:19:05,250
No, that’s not important
right now.

438
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:08,320
Why are you strutting around,
carrying a hand in your bag?

439
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:09,560
That’s so freaky!

440
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:11,760
Kira: You’re by yourself,
i presume?

441
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:13,860
i don’t see
your playmates anywhere.

442
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:16,600
I believe their names
were josuke and okuyasu?

443
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:18,300
Would it be safe to assume

444
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:20,370
they both have powers
similar to ours?

445
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,500
shigechi: Oh, no!
Don’t you move a single muscle!

446
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:26,270
If you so much as blink,
you’re a goner!

447
00:19:26,310 --> 00:19:28,740
My gut’s sayin’ you’re
some kind of closet weirdo,

448
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:30,540
and I don’t want you
coming any closer,

449
00:19:30,580 --> 00:19:33,150
so stay there if you know
what’s good for you!

450
00:19:33,180 --> 00:19:34,580
Just looking at your slimy face

451
00:19:34,620 --> 00:19:36,550
is starting
to make my skin crawl.

452
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:40,220
You’re evil, and evil people
need to stay far away. Ahh!

453
00:19:41,790 --> 00:19:44,390
Kira: You can call me
yoshikage Kira.

454
00:19:44,430 --> 00:19:46,330
I’m currently 33 years old.

455
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,800
Not that you’d care,

456
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:50,470
but I reside in northeast
morioh’s villa district.

457
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,970
Also, i’ve yet to marry.

458
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,970
( Shigechi gasping )

459
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,700
Kira: In order to make a living,

460
00:19:55,740 --> 00:19:57,710
I work for kameyu
department stores.

461
00:19:57,740 --> 00:19:59,270
After a long day’s work,

462
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:01,380
I return home
no later than 8 P.M.

463
00:20:01,410 --> 00:20:02,940
( Shigechi gasps )

464
00:20:02,980 --> 00:20:04,650
Kira: I don’t like smoking,

465
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:06,650
but do enjoy
the occasional drink.

466
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,880
I’m always in bed by 11 P.M.,
and I make it a point

467
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,420
to get no less than eight hours
of sleep each night.

468
00:20:12,450 --> 00:20:13,750
Shigechi: Uh...

469
00:20:13,790 --> 00:20:16,490
kira: Before bed,
I drink a warm glass of milk.

470
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:18,630
it’s always coupled
with 20 minutes of stretching

471
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:20,530
to decompress
from the long workday.

472
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:22,900
sweet dreams are
the usual result of this.

473
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,300
Shigechi: Eh...

474
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:25,930
Kira: I then awake as refreshed

475
00:20:25,970 --> 00:20:27,800
and recharged
as a newborn child,

476
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,800
ready to take on
the day’s challenges.

477
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,870
And after my last checkup, I was
given a clean bill of health.

478
00:20:32,910 --> 00:20:34,980
shigechi: Hey,
what’s the big idea, creeper?

479
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:36,840
Why are telling me this crap?

480
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,610
Kira: For as long
as I can remember,

481
00:20:38,650 --> 00:20:40,980
i’ve done everything in my power
to live a productive life

482
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:43,720
that allows me to pursue
a lasting, inner peace.

483
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:45,490
This may be a foreign concept,

484
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:48,560
but I choose not to concern
myself with winning or losing,

485
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:50,960
life’s troubles, or enemies
who bring sleepless nights.

486
00:20:50,990 --> 00:20:52,530
That is how I cope

487
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,760
with this backwards life
we find ourselves living.

488
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,670
It’s what brings me happiness

489
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:58,730
in a world fraught
with hardship and misery.

490
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:03,340
Of course, if I were
